----------------------
Server News
----------------------

1. SGI Uncloaks Linux Super Servers
January 7, 2003
The systems maker claimed Tuesday that its new Altix 3000 line of Linux-based 
servers and software shatters performance and scalability records. 
http://www.serverwatch.com/news/article.php/1565331

------------------------------------------------------------ 
2. Macromedia Updates ColdFusion for J2EE, Adds OS Support
January 7, 2003
In a sweeping move, Macromedia Tuesday announced additions to its ColdFusion MX 
for J2EE Application Servers product family and added Mac OS X and AIX support.
http://www.serverwatch.com/news/article.php/1565241

------------------------------------------------------------ 
3. Solaris 'wall' Vulnerability Can Spoof Message Senders
January 6, 2003
Solaris' 'wall' program, a long-time UNIX favorite, can be made to send messages
that appear to originate from any user, including a system administrator. 
http://www.serverwatch.com/news/article.php/1564941

------------------------------------------------------------ 
4. Kerio Centers Latest Version of Mail Server Around Collaborative Apps
January 3, 2003
The latest version of Kerio MailServer features managed contacts and 
communication capabilities. It also lays claim to being the first non-Microsoft 
mail server to fully integrate with Active Directory.
http://www.serverwatch.com/news/article.php/1563891

------------------------------------------------------------ 
5. December 2002 Security Space Survey Results 
January 2, 2003
Security Space's Web Server Survey breaks out Web server software usage on the 
Internet for 86 domains. Data for the December survey was gathered from 
responses received from more than 8.5 million Web sites. More than 4.6 million 
of these sites are .com domains. 
http://www.serverwatch.com/news/article.php/1563451

------------------------------------------------------------ 


