---------------------------------
Related Stories
---------------------------------

Server coverage isn't limited to ServerWatch! 
Other internet.com sites also discuss servers and server-related issues. 
In this section of the newsletter, we highlight relevant stories that 
have run on internet.com sites within the past week.


** SharePoint: Reviewing the New Features in Version 2
The new capabilities in SharePoint Portal Server version 2 are likely to 
include sign-on, user and application management services, and personalization. 
http://networking.earthweb.com/netos/article/0,,12083_1563111,00.html

------------------------------------------------------------ 
** IBM Takes a Building Brick Approach with 'IceCube'
The company's Silicon Valley labs have come up with a working model of a dense 
cluster of servers, storage, and switches built up as a 3D cubic array. 
http://siliconvalley.internet.com/news/article.php/1564071

------------------------------------------------------------ 
** Transmeta Enters Embedded Fray with Crusoe SE
The Santa Clara, Calif.-based chipmaker configured its x86-compatible low-power
Crusoes to withstand harsh environments -- like an automobile or a refrigerator. 
http://siliconvalley.internet.com/news/article.php/1564531

------------------------------------------------------------ 
 


---------------------------------
Feature Articles
---------------------------------

1. Learn AD in 15 Minutes a Week: Microsoft DNS - Part 2
January 6, 2003
Part 18 of Jason Zandri's 'Learn Active Directory Design and Administration in 
15 Minutes a Week' series takes a second look at Microsoft DNS and reverse 
lookups and caching, as well as some of the local records that the DNS server 
holds.
http://www.serverwatch.com/tutorials/article.php/1564421

------------------------------------------------------------ 
2. Finding Depth and Breadth in WinGate Pro 5.0
January 2, 2003
Designed for the enterprise sharing an Internet connection on a LAN, WinGate Pro
is one of the most complete proxy systems on the market. In addition to the top
-of-the-line proxy server at its core, the server offers an e-mail server, spam 
filtering, and a full suite of plug-in features. But as thorough as WinGate Pro 
is, it's not for the less technically savvy or the impatient. 
http://www.serverwatch.com/sreviews/article.php/1563501

